Health officials in Hong Kong are investigating the deadly H5N1 strain of bird flu that has caused global concern.
The virus has claimed lives, with a 3-year-old boy and a man succumbing to the illness.
Efforts are being made to trace the source of the infection, with poultry farms under scrutiny.
Authorities are considering the development of a vaccine, while emphasizing the importance of hygiene and proper food preparation.
Despite concerns, experts reassure the public that the risk of human-to-human transmission is low.
Vigilance and precautionary measures are advised to prevent further spread of the virus.
